var e=`http://localhost:3001/api`;async function t(t,n){let r=n?`?month=${n}`:``,i=await fetch(`${e}/products/${t}/availability${r}`);if(!i.ok)throw Error(`Failed to fetch availability`);return i.json()}async function n(t,n){let r=await fetch(`${e}/rentals`,{method:`POST`,headers:{"Content-Type":`application/json`,Authorization:`Bearer ${n}`},body:JSON.stringify(t)});if(!r.ok){let e=await r.json();throw Error(e.error||`Failed to create rental`)}return r.json()}async function r(t,n){let r=n?`?status=${n}`:``,i=await fetch(`${e}/rentals${r}`,{headers:{Authorization:`Bearer ${t}`}});if(!i.ok)throw Error(`Failed to fetch rentals`);return i.json()}async function i(t,n,r){let i=await fetch(`${e}/rentals/${t}/status`,{method:`PATCH`,headers:{"Content-Type":`application/json`,Authorization:`Bearer ${r}`},body:JSON.stringify({status:n})});if(!i.ok){let e=await i.json();throw Error(e.error||`Failed to update status`)}return i.json()}export{i,t as n,r,n as t};